hopobject.body: I'm sorry, I'm not interested duodart 0 4 mg There are some false notes: the single non-Irish monologue is from Vasya, a migrant who flocked to benefit from Ireland’s property bubble, winding up another victim of Pokey Burke’s crookedness. (Burke, tellingly, is the one figure who does not give an account of himself.) Vasya’s poetic tone rings false; in other sections, it seems unlikely that such a small locale can produce not one but three potential psychopaths.
